                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Talwar aide   cries torture
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                                              Krishna at the court on Monday. (PTI)		        
	New Delhi, June 23: Dentist Rajesh Talwars compounder, Krishna, today told a court the CBI was torturing him during interrogation on the Aarushi-Hemraj murders.        
	During the hearing, which ended with a four-day extension of his remand, Krishna also claimed he was innocent.        
	Aarushis mother Nupur was questioned yesterday. Although the agency didnt reveal the nature of the questions, sources said she was confronted with certain facts that had emerged from Talwars last polygraph test.        
	According to the sources, it was clear that all those being questioned  the Talwar couple, their friends and business partners Anita and Praful Durrani, their domestic help Rajkumar and a neighbours servant, Vijay Mandal  know something about the murders, or the circumstances leading to them.                                                                                                                                                                          
